    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "32f04026_104853f0",
        "filename": "golden/go/publicparams/publicparams_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 29,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-11T20:34:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Let\u0027s limit greek letters to one thing only (the corpus), otherwise things become a bit confusing to read.\n\nModels, SDKs and tests can be defined as:\n\n  model1 \u003d \"model1\"\n  model2 \u003d \"model2\"\n  sdk1 \u003d \"sdk1\"\n  ...\n  test1 \u003d \"test1\"\n  ...\n\nAny other naming scheme is fine as long as things of different kinds are completely distinct.\n\nOn second thought, I don\u0027t think defining these constants is necessary. Using raw strings in the test cases is probably fine, especially considering they\u0027re defined all in one single place, and the constants aren\u0027t used for anything else. But the naming suggestion still holds.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 20,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 29,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "1e2f6add59ba343ec1a26b23efa9ccfa3ad019fd",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d0a69818_17cd8abb",
        "filename": "golden/go/publicparams/publicparams_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 29,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-12T12:26:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I prefer the constants as it makes it harder to mistype something. I went with your suggestion about greek letters.",
      "parentUuid": "32f04026_104853f0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 20,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 29,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "1e2f6add59ba343ec1a26b23efa9ccfa3ad019fd",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "429a4ca4_c70dce3d",
        "filename": "golden/go/publicparams/publicparams_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 48,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-11T20:34:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since these are effectively test cases, I would recommend sticking to the same naming rules we use for any other test cases. In particular:\n\n- Name these after the behavior/rule under test, rather than the names of the keys/values.\n- Include the expected outcome in the test name. Currently the reader needs to scroll down to the test function to get this information.\n- Use a consistent naming pattern, e.g. \u003ccorpus\u003e_\u003cother key/values\u003e_\u003cexpected outcome\u003e.\n\nSuggested name for the highlighted test case:\n  knownCorpus_unknownKey_valid",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 48,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "1e2f6add59ba343ec1a26b23efa9ccfa3ad019fd",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3368f958_16bf25be",
        "filename": "golden/go/publicparams/publicparams_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 48,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-12T12:26:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I can rename them as testcases. Originally, I had two Matchers, so it didn\u0027t make sense to specify how they should be Matched, but ended up removing one. I\u0027ll go with a slightly different naming convention to what you proposed.",
